features: UNSCENTED BABY WIPES. No alcohol, SLS, formaldehyde, parabens, or fragrance. Uses naturally derived ingredients saline solution safe for ingestion – you don’t even have to rinse off the wipe residue.
SALINE SOLUTION WIPES. Gently clean damaged skin. individual wrapped, easy to open. These packs may be kept in a first aid kit , diaper bag essential items or with health care supplies.
PACIFIER AND BOTTLE WIPES. Perfect portable solution to safely and naturally clean pacifiers, bottles, teethers, cups, toys, feeding spoons and more.
SALINE WATER WIPE. Cleans what your baby spits out. Wipe away saliva, pacifier dirt, dust, and other unwanted travelers while you’re at home or on the go.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: On a trip and had to clean an incision daily. These were perfect for traveling! Will definitely buy again!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Difficult to unwrap and smell is odd.
reviews.reviewText: I wanted just saline in a wipe. I don't know or sure if that is all that is in the wipe (saline) because they smell odd. The wipe is smaller than I expected. Unfolding it takes time and maybe long finger nails. The wipe material is nice and smooth. I will keep looking for a solution. UPDATE: Company issued a refund. Very customer focused! Changed from 2 stars to 3.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I use it to wipe my kids faces. Best thing to clean their eyes with. It's way cheaper that the kids brands that they sell out there.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars CAME WITH MOLD!
reviews.reviewText: Please BEWARE! I bought two boxes for my newborn who had a eye that was healing from an infection and one of the boxes had a few wipes that had MOLD on them! Immediately threw all away!! I also noticed that using these (used for 3 weeks) never seemed to really help with the discharge in my baby’s eye until I bought a different brand and within days, the discharge was gone. Maybe I happened to be unlucky but it’s unacceptable!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Try another brand
reviews.reviewText: Arrived with one side of the plastic protective packaging open (maybe this was a return). The sheets are small and made out of paper with a very small amount of saline solution. I’m not sure why they would make a saline wipe out of paper. It scratched my skin and really didn’t do what it was meant to do, which is safely clean an area of the skin. Disappointed and would like a refund.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2022
reviews.reviewText: These have a funky smell. The wipe itself is okay- a bit thinner than I expected, but I'm okay with that. I just can't get over the smell.
